Team description: 
 
The main aim of the accountants/analysts in the OTC Derivatives Support Team is to of understand the terms of all derivatives contracts and to accurately record these products on BNY Mellon accounting system. It involves capturing the trades but also monitoring the life cycle of the derivatives: ensuring rates are updated, cash settlements are reconciled to BNY Mellon Custody and positions are reconciled to counterparties. The team is also responsible for the investigation and resolution of all derivative breaks and queries through communication with custody, client and counterparty. 
 
 
Main responsibilities of the candidate to the role:
 
As a skilled Lead Representative in the OTC Derivatives Support Team you will play a vital role helping us to automate the processes the team is performing daily and to provide the support to the existing tools/applications we are using. Key aspects of the role include:


 Building knowledge of the OTC Derivatives Support Team processes (trade capture, broker reconciliation, lifecycle management);  

 Develop an understanding of all the technical functions and processes in the team; 

 Working on the new functionalities/tools being created/introduced to the team by being involved in their configuration, mapping and their adjustment to the team processes; 

 Providing support for legacy tools/applications by being the first line support, investigating issues and providing resolutions;  

 Strive to improve standards within the team; adopt questioning approach to current methods and provide viable alternatives where possible; 

 When working on projects, effectively communicating progress to colleagues and management at all levels;  

 Provide trainings to the team if new tools/functionalities are being introduced to make sure the knowledge is spread across the team. 
 Qualifications 

 University degree; 

 2+ years of professional experience, preferably in finance or related areas; 

 Very confident computer user, comfortable learning new tools and programmes quickly; 

 Excellent knowledge of Microsoft Excel and other office programmes and an interest in enhancing these skills further; 

 VBA knowledge will be an asset; 

 Xceptor knowledge will be an advantage; 

 A results orientated individual who has a logical and analytical method of working; 

 Ability to learn quickly and to grasp the intricacies of complex over-the-counter (OTC) derivatives; 

 Ability to work on own initiative/project when required, as well as in the team; 

 Effective oral and written communication skills; 

 Highly motivated, reliable, well organised.  
What we can offer you:

Full time contract of employment
Competitive salary
Health & Life Insurance
Multisport card / Cinema Tickets / Nursery subsidiary
Pension scheme
Excellent opportunities for training, growth and professional development
Opportunities to engage in diverse projects due to growth of business migrations
A multitude of opportunities to get involved in additional charity projects
3 volunteering days per annum
A collaborative culture and great teams
